Durban - In their commitment to eradicate the scourge of the drugs in the province KZN police conducted a raid in Umhlanga and recovered over R200 000 worth of drugs. Armed with a search warrant police officers embarked on a joint multi-disciplinary operation was conducted at Umhlanga to follow up on intelligence with regards to a drug den. KZN police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane said  1094 heroin capsules, 1611 mandrax tablets, 11000 empty capsules, 689  ecstasy pills, 70g crushed ecstasy pills, 10g heroin powder and 754g of bulking powder were recovered. The estimated street value of recovered drugs is R227 770. A 39-year-old woman was arrested and charged with dealing in drugs. She is expected to make her first appearance in the Verulam Magistrate's Court. "The seized drugs will be subjected to forensic analysis," said Zwane. In a seperate incident six suspects were arrested for possession of drugs by the eThekwini Outer South Cluster yesterday. Police officers conducted operations targeting drug dealers at Umlazi, Folweni and Amanzimtoti. POST